HEADWORD: Lherzolite
<hw>Lher"zo*lite</hw> <pr>(l⟦etil⟧r"z⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From <ets>Lherz</ets>, a place in the Pyrenees +
<ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An igneous rock
consisting largely of chrysolite, with pyroxene and picotite (a variety
of spinel containing chromium).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

